commit.message: Make dependencies in README and debian/control more consistent

Fix appindicator fallback import

Before it was trying the fallback import even if the first choice
import succeeded. This resulted in confusing diagnostic messages about
failing to import the fallback on systems that only have the first
choice.

commit.message: Improve "how to release new version" docs
Start version 2.0.1

Release v2.0

fluxgui (2.0) wily; urgency=low

  * add support for Redshift as the backend
      https://github.com/xflux-gui/fluxgui/pull/143.

 -- Nathan Collins <nathan.collins@gmail.com>  Wed, 28 Sep 2022
 20:51:26 +0800
Merge branch 'pr/redshift_support'
Update changelog
Update README for Redshift support
Use Redshift backend by default for new installs

Print backend command lines before running them

Helps with debugging and makes it clear that we're attempting to run
the backend when xflux fails silently.
Document how to read and reset gsettings

Make Redshift color changes happen immediately

This fixes the preview functionality, and makes settings changes take
effect immediately.

Fix logic of lat+long settings check for Redshift

The Redshift backend requires that *both* the latitude and longitude
be set, but the logic in some places was only checking if *either* of
them were set, since that's what the analogous logic in the xflux
backend does (i.e. for xflux *either* the zip or the latitude must be
set).
Ignore pyenv local settings
Warn that PPA is way out of date

commit.message: stop redshift from being restarted everytime after the Preferences window closes when the user change some setting

Fix KeywordError when only changing latitude

If the user change only the latitude the program will use the last
saved value for the longitude, the same logic happens if only
longitude changes. And only set the location option to redshift
if the latitude or longitude changes.
